    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_ird" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>ird</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>светлый</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>bright</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ясный</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>clear</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>ird bon</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>ясный день</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>light day</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>ra-ird</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>прояснилось</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>(the sky) cleared up</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>cæstitæ ird æma sænt saw</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>глаза ясные и черные-черные</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the eyes are clear and very black</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>69</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>arvi st’alutæ cæfsuncæ, æj æxsævæ ird, kæʒos</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>на небе горят звезды, ночь ясна, чиста</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the starts are shining in the sky, the night is cloudless and
                                clear</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>63</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>zujmon mæjroxsæj ird ærttivtoncæ Digori xwænxtæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>в зимнюю лунную ночь ясным светом сияли горы Дигории</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>in winter moonlit night the mountains of Digoria shone with clear
                                light</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Sozur"/><biblScope>60</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>æ tæfælttæ ærxawdtæncæ, ni-jbæl-tar æj æ ird bon</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>опустились его веки, померк над ним ясный день</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>his eyes fell shut, the clear day darkened over him</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Qazb."/><biblScope>69</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>me rtajæn — sawædoni ird sug æj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>моя купальня — прозрачная струя родника</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>my bathhouse is a transparent spring stream</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Saxi_ræs."
                                /><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Закономерно восходит к иран. *%iidra-%i или *%ividra%i (в
                    последнем случае с обычным отпадением %iv%i перед %ii%i). Ср. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>*idhra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>vīdhra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>светлый</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ясный</q></gloss></mentioned>, особенно о небе: ‘ясное небо’, от
                    корня %iidh-%i (и.е. *%iaidh-%i, *%iidh-%i) ‘сиять’ и пр.; сюда же <mentioned
                        xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>αίθήρ</w>
                        <gloss><q>светлое небесное пространство</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>эфир</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                            ><w>αίθρα</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>αίθρία</w>
                        <gloss><q>ясное небо</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ясный, прозрачный воздух</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ясная погода</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                            ><w>αίθριος</w>
                        <gloss><q>ясный</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>светлый</q></gloss></mentioned>. На иранской почве сюда можно
                    относить, быть может, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/>
                        <w>īra</w>
                        <gloss><q>яркость</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ясность</q></gloss></mentioned> (заимствовано из <mentioned
                        xml:lang="psh"><lang/>
                        <w>īr</w>
                        <gloss><q>ясное небо</q></gloss></mentioned>?. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>I 235</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>ləroɣo</w>
                        <gloss><q>ясное небо</q></gloss></mentioned> (из *%iid-raka%i?). Ср. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_irdgæ"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                    224</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It naturally traces back to Iranian *%iidra-%i or *%ividra%i (in
                    the latter case with the usual omission of %iv%i before %ii%i). Cf. <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>*idhra-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>vīdhra-</w>
                        <gloss><q>light</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>clear</q></gloss></mentioned>, especially of the sky: ‘clear sky’,
                    from the root %iidh-%i (Indo-European *%iaidh-%i, *%iidh-%i) ‘to shine’ etc.;
                        <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>αίθήρ</w>
                        <gloss><q>light air space</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>ether</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                            ><w>αίθρα</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w>αίθρία</w>
                        <gloss><q>clear sky</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>clear, transparent air</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fair weather</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                            ><w>αίθριος</w>
                        <gloss><q>clear</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>light</q></gloss></mentioned> are related here too. In the Iranian
                    context <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><lang/>
                        <w>īra</w>
                        <gloss><q>brightness</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="prc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>clearness</q></gloss></mentioned> (borrowed from <mentioned
                        xml:lang="psh"><lang/>
                        <w>īr</w>
                        <gloss><q>clear sky</q></gloss></mentioned>?. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>I 235</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>ləroɣo</w>
                        <gloss><q>clear sky</q></gloss></mentioned> (from *%iid-raka%i?) might be
                    related here as well. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_irdgæ"/>.%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                            224</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
